    {
        "title": "What Are Inequalities?",
        "body": "<h3>Beyond Equations: Introducing Inequalities</h3><p>While equations say equals (x = 5), inequalities express ranges and bounds. In the real world, we rarely have exact values: speed LIMITS mean \\(v \\leq 60\\) mph, minimum ages mean \\(a \\geq 13\\), budgets mean \\(c < 500\\).</p><p>An inequality compares two expressions using four symbols:</p><ul><li>\\(x < 5\\) — x is strictly less than 5</li><li>\\(x > 5\\) — x is strictly greater than 5</li><li>\\(x \\leq 5\\) — x is less than or equal to 5</li><li>\\(x \\geq 5\\) — x is greater than or equal to 5</li></ul><p>The solution is not a single number, but a set of all numbers satisfying the condition.</p>"
    },
